productDetails.productTitle: UMIDIGI Note 100A Cell Phone, 6.8" HD+ 120Hz Display Phones, Android 14 Unlocked Smartphone, 8(4+4)+256GB/1TB TF, 5000mAh Battery Andriod Phone, AI Face & Fingerprint Unlock, 4G Dual SIM, GPS,OTG
featureBullets: 𝐀𝐧𝐝𝐫𝐨𝐢𝐝 𝟏𝟒 𝐒𝐲𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐦: The UMIDIGI Note 100A smart phone, running Android 14, provides a more personalized and secure experience by optimizing the interface, enhancing privacy, and improving overall performance

𝟖(𝟒+𝟒)+𝟐𝟓𝟔𝐆𝐁/𝟏𝐓𝐁 𝐓𝐅: The UMIDIGI Note 100A unlocked cell phone features an 8GB RAM and 256GB ROM configuration, with support for up to 1TB TF card expansion. It also offers dual SIM slots that can accommodate Dual Nano SIM cards or a combination of a Nano SIM and a TF card

𝟏𝟐𝟎𝐇𝐳+𝟔.𝟖𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐡 𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐲: The UMIDIGI Note 100A mobile phone features a 6.8-inch display with a resolution of 1600×720 pixels and an aspect ratio of 20:9. The screen supports a 120Hz refresh rate, providing a smooth viewing experience

𝟓𝟎𝟎𝟎𝐦𝐀𝐡 𝐁𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐲: The UMIDIGI Note 100A android phone unlocked owns a 5000mAh long-lasting battery, supporting 20W PD fast charging, which significantly reduces charging time. It also comes with a standard 10W charger

𝐅𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐞𝐫𝐩𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐭+𝐀𝐈 𝐅𝐚𝐜𝐞 𝐔𝐧𝐥𝐨𝐜𝐤: The Note 100A umidigi phone features dual unlock options, including a side-mounted fingerprint sensor and AI Face Unlock. This combination provides users with both convenience and security

𝟏𝟑𝐌𝐏 + 𝟖𝐌𝐏+ 𝟐𝐌𝐏 𝐂𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐚: The UMIDIGI Note 100A unlocked phone is equipped with a dual-camera setup, consisting of a 13MP main camera and a 2MP macro camera, along with an 8MP front camera. The camera system supports various modes like Panorama, Night Mode, and Time-lapse
𝐌𝐮𝐥𝐭𝐢-𝐅𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐏𝐡𝐨𝐧𝐞: The UMIDIGI Note 100A android 14 phone features a comprehensive set of functionalities, including FM Radio with a headphone jack, OTG support, GPS, and Bluetooth 5.2

𝐀 𝐘𝐞𝐚𝐫 𝐀𝐟𝐭𝐞𝐫-𝐬𝐚𝐥𝐞𝐬 𝐒𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞: We provide 1 year after-sales service and support. You can find us through the "Service Center App" on your phone, which is our specialized after-sales service software. First way, enter the "Customer Service" and then click the "Questions"
